HEADWORD: Eurotiales
<hw>Eurotiales</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an order of fungi having a closed
ascocarp (cleistothecium) with the asci scattered rather than gathered
into a hymenial layer.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> order <ord>Eurotiales</ord>, Aspergillales, order
<ord>Aspergillales</ord>.</syn>⟦br⟧
